posts.raw_content:
**Sponsored Bills (Primary Introducer)**

**119th Congress (2025):**

H.R.276: Gulf of America Act – Introduced Jan 2025; renames Gulf of Mexico; referred to committee.

H.R.1862: English Language Unity Act of 2025 – Introduced Mar 5, 2025; makes English official language; referred to committees.

H.R.3492: Protect Children’s Innocence Act – Introduced May 19, 2025; bans gender-affirming care for minors, punishable by up to 25 years; reported by Judiciary Committee, placed on calendar (advanced but not passed).

H.R.4327: No Tax on Home Sales Act – Introduced Jul 2025; eliminates taxes on home sales; referred to committee.

H.R.4403: Clear Skies Act – Introduced Jul 15, 2025; addresses environmental or aviation policies; referred to Energy and Commerce.

H.R.4798: Making American Elections Great Again Act – Introduced Jul 29, 2025; election integrity reforms; referred to multiple committees.

Other 119th sponsored: Includes resolutions on Epstein files release, H-1B phase-out, and amendments to foreign aid bills (e.g., requiring pro-Ukraine aid voters to enlist in Ukrainian military; failed but garnered attention).

**118th Congress (2023-2025):**

H.Res.863: Impeaching Alejandro Mayorkas – Introduced Nov 2023; historic impeachment of DHS Secretary for border policies; passed House Feb 2024 (dismissed by Senate).

H.R.528: Stop the Cartels Act – Introduced Jan 2023; anti-cartel measures; referred to committee.

H.R.1136: Protect Children's Innocence Act – Introduced Feb 2023; similar to 119th version, anti-trans care; referred to committee.

H.Res.396: Impeaching Biden – Introduced May 2023; articles of impeachment; referred to committee.

H.R.6237: Social Security Integrity Act – Introduced Nov 2023; reforms SSA; referred to committee.

**Other notable:** Amendments to NDAA defunding NATO/Ukraine aid (some passed House); bills on COVID origins probes, anti-vaccine mandate.

**117th Congress (2021-2023):**

H.Res.57: Impeaching Biden – Introduced Jan 2021; first of several; referred to committee.

H.R.607: Articles of Impeachment Against Biden – Introduced Jan 2021; similar; referred.

H.R.2316: Fire Fauci Act – Introduced Apr 2021; reduces Fauci's salary to $0; referred to committee.

H.R.2317: We Will Not Comply Act – Introduced Apr 2021; blocks vaccine mandates; referred.

H.R.7613: 21st Century FREE Speech Act – Introduced Apr 2022; protects online speech; referred.

H.R.29: Protect America First Act – Introduced Jan 2021; immigration restrictions; referred.

**Co-Sponsored Bills**

**Key themes:** Anti-immigration (e.g., co-sponsored H.R.2 Secure the Border Act, passed House 2023), 2nd Amendment (e.g., concealed carry reciprocity), anti-trans/LGBTQ (e.g., Old Glory Only Act banning embassy pride flags, 2021), election integrity, and opposing foreign aid. 

**Notable examples:**

Old Glory Only Act (H.R.529, 2021) – Bans non-U.S. flags at embassies; co-sponsored Feb 2, 2021.

Human Trafficking Prevention Act of 2022 (co-sponsored; became law).

Faster Payments to Veterans' Survivors Act of 2022 (co-sponsored; became law).

H.Res.581 (119th) – Procedural on policy advancement; co-sponsored.

Numerous symbolic ones like renaming post offices (e.g., John Lewis USPS office, 2022) and censures (e.g., against Rep. Tlaib, 2023).


So glad shes leaving. This is definitely a win! /s
